latestPosts.caption:
Met so many beautiful souls here in Mayapur… I mean I was never this outspoken… used to be the shyest girl in school… but something about connecting with people… with energies… feels like home to my heart…

When you surrender… when you just do your karma and leave the rest to Him… life flows differently… softer… kinder… fuller…

The rituals here aren’t just traditions… they’re reminders… to slow down… to be present… to live with love and purpose…

That’s the whole point, isn’t it? To live happy… to give love… to feel peace… and to keep coming back to yourself…

Harinaam in the air… kindness in the people… and Krishna in every heartbeat…

“Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare
Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare”

A simple chant… yet so powerful… calling the divine names to cleanse the heart, calm the mind, and awaken pure love within ✨🕊️
#mayapur
